    What does Pant mean?
    1. a. : to breathe quickly, spasmodically, or in a labored manner. b. : to run panting.

    What is the qualification of Rishabh Pant?
    AI Overview
    Rishabh Pant, the Indian cricketer, holds a Bachelor of Commerce (B.Com) degree from Sri Venkateswara College, Delhi University. He completed his schooling at the Indian Public School, Dehradun. 
    Here's a more detailed breakdown:
    • Schooling: He attended the Indian Public School in Dehradun. 
    • Higher Education: He earned his B.Com degree from Sri Venkateswara College, Delhi University. 
    • Cricket Focus: Despite his academic pursuits, Pant prioritized his cricket training and participated in various tournaments. 
    • Born: He was born on October 4, 1997, in Roorkee, Uttarakhand. 
    • Early Training: He started his cricket training at Sonnet Cricket Academy in Delhi at the age of 12 and was coached by Tarak Sinha. 
    • Represented Rajasthan: He represented Rajasthan at U-14 and U-16 levels.

      Do you say Pant or pants?
      Think of items that are usually referred to in pluraloften preceded by pair of or something similar, even when there is only one item: pliers, glasses, scissors, sunglasses, tweezers, etc. So, pants is a type of noun that is used only in its plural form, even when there is only one item being discussed.

      Rishabh Rajendra Pant is an Indian international cricketer who plays for the Indian cricket team as a wicket-keeper batter. He captains and plays for the Lucknow Super Giants in the Indian Premier League. Having played all formats for India, he is best known for his consistency to score runs in Test cricket. Wikipedia
